  "text": "The fact that three schemes (MADA, Fu, and Yang) in Figs. 13 and 14 predict nearly the same ␤ abs,m for D e Ͻ 160 m suggests that the spectral differences in the window region regarding the Yang scheme (in relation to the MADA and Fu schemes; see Fig. 10 ) tend to cancel regarding their contributions to ␤ abs,m . The close agreement among these schemes also suggests that radiative processes were parameterized fairly accurately in MADA, and that the bimodal behavior of the SDs assumed in the Fu and Yang schemes was not too dissimilar to that of the SD schemes employed here [CITATION_1] . However, note that this agreement is partially due to the use of T e corresponding to hexagonal columns, which may not be representative of ice crystals in cirrus clouds.",
